The paper deals with algorithms for solving the minimum multicut problem in graphs embedded on surfaces, which involves graph theory, topology, and computational geometry. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) are likely categories. Additionally, the paper involves optimization and combinatorial algorithms, which are relevant to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
